            <fileData><![CDATA[<#-- title: EPDM -->
<main class="pt-28 pb-16">
    <section class="max-w-container mx-auto px-4 md:px-12 py-8">
        <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">EPDM Liners</h1>
        <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed">
            <p>
                EPDM (Ethylene Propylene Diene Terpolymer) is a synthetic rubber, which gives it much
                more elasticity than other liner materials. EPDM is a beginner-friendly material that
                is most common in small koi ponds, with excellent resistance to UV and harsh
                environmental conditions.
            </p>
            <p>
                Pipe penetrations are made easily by cutting an undersized hole and stretching the
                liner over the pipe. Note that the hole must be round to evenly distribute the stress
                around the circumference.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="l-glass rounded-2xl p-8 mt-10 max-w-3xl">
            <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mb-4">At a glance</h2>
            <dl class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-x-8 gap-y-3 text-sm">
                <div><dt class="text-outline font-label">Standard thickness</dt><dd class="text-on-surface">45 mil</dd></div>
                <div><dt class="text-outline font-label">Standard roll sizes</dt><dd class="text-on-surface">10'&ndash;50' wide, 100'&ndash;200' long</dd></div>
                <div><dt class="text-outline font-label">Seaming method</dt><dd class="text-on-surface">Tape</dd></div>
                <div><dt class="text-outline font-label">Minimum order</dt><dd class="text-on-surface">None, partial rolls available</dd></div>
            </dl>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8">
            <a href="/content/contact" class="bg-primary hover:bg-primary/90 text-on-primary font-label text-sm font-medium px-6 py-3 rounded-lg l-glow transition-all inline-flex items-center gap-2">
                Get a quote
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>
</main>]]></fileData>
